                 <div class="txtNew" data-packed="false" id="comp-j3rphqm0" style="top:339px;bottom:;left:51px;right:;width:408px;height:auto;position:absolute">
                  <p class="font_8" style="font-size:14px;">
                   <span style="font-family:arial, ,ms pgothic,,dotum,helvetica,sans-serif;">
                    <span style="font-size:14px;">
                     <span class="color_11">
                      With an overall population of 15,000, the Creston valley is a vibrant and rapidly transforming community that continues to draw dynamic and entrepreneurial people to the region. Located along southern British Columbia's major transportation corridor, Creston's age-friendly environment,high levels of civic engagement andrange of local attractions make for a highly liveable regionand premiere tourism and business re-location destination.
                     </span>
                    </span>
                   </span>
                  </p>
                  <p class="font_8" style="font-size:14px;">
                  </p>
                  <p class="font_8" style="font-size:14px;">
                   <span style="font-family:arial, ,ms pgothic,,dotum,helvetica,sans-serif;">
                    <span style="font-size:14px;">
                     <span class="color_11">
                      Complemented by astrong arts community, a progressive and expanding food and agricultural sector, andexcellentbroadband capacity, Creston is anemerging jewel in the Kootenay region crown.
                     </span>
                    </span>
                   </span>
                  </p>
                  <p class="font_8" style="font-size:14px;">
                  </p>
                  <p class="font_8" style="font-size:14px;">
                   <span style="font-family:arial, ,ms pgothic,,dotum,helvetica,sans-serif;">
                    <span style="font-size:14px;">
                     <span class="color_11">
                      A member of the British Columbia Chamber of Commerce, the
                      <span style="font-weight:bold;">
                       Creston Valley Chamber of Commerce
                      </span>
                      is the most public, influential and active advocate for business in the region. We co-locate with the Creston Visitor Centre in our building at 121 NW Blvd (see map below). You can reach us by calling 250-428-5151 during regular office hours.
                     </span>
                    </span>
                   </span>
                  </p>
                  <p class="font_8" style="font-size:14px;">
                   <span style="font-family:arial, ,ms pgothic,,dotum,helvetica,sans-serif;">
                    <span style="font-size:14px;">
                     <span class="wixGuard">
                      
                     </span>
                    </span>
                   </span>
                  </p>
                  <p class="font_8" style="font-size:14px;">
                   <span style="font-family:arial, ,ms pgothic,,dotum,helvetica,sans-serif;">
                    <span style="font-size:14px;">
                     <span class="color_11">
                      For more information about what a Chamber of Commerce is as an organization and what it does for its members, please read our
                      <span style="text-decoration:underline;">
                       <a href="https://www.crestonvalleychamber.com/chamber-faq" target="_self">
                        Frequently Asked Questions
                       </a>
                      </span>
                      .
                     </span>
                    </span>
                   </span>
                  </p>

Work&nbsp;<\/span><\/span><\/span><\/p>\n\n<p class=\"font_8\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">The Creston Valley Chamber of Commerce is seeking original poster and logo designs for its Gran Fondo event planned for September, 2019.&nbsp;&ldquo;Gran Fondo&rdquo; is Italian for &ldquo;the big ride,&rdquo; and the Chamber is looking to promote Creston, along with the Okanagan and Cranbrook, as one of the premiere Gran Fondo events in western Canada.&nbsp;The Creston Gran Fondo ride routes will take in Canyon-Lister, Arrow mountain and the lake road as far as just south of Gray Creek.<\/span><\/p>\n\n<p class=\"font_8\" style=\"line-height:1.1em\"><br \/>\n<span style=\"color:#000000\">Two primary design components are required &mdash; a poster and a logo -- and possibly class=\"wixGuard\"><\/span><\/span><\/p>\n\n<p class=\"font_8\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">Poster image&nbsp;&mdash; with the following elements:<\/span><\/p>\n\n<p class=\"font_8\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">Foreground:&nbsp;fields\/farms\/valley<\/span><\/p>\n\n<p class=\"font_8\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">Midground:&nbsp;rolling hills and lake<\/span><\/p>\n\n<p class=\"font_8\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">Background:&nbsp;mountains<br \/>\nAlso, likely midground:&nbsp;an Osprey in flight, likely over the lake;&nbsp;a key element is a road that winds its way from foreground imagery to running alongside the lake in the midground.&nbsp;Road must be prominent, as this after all is a road biking event.&nbsp;One or more riders on bicycles need also to be included &mdash; likely as part of the road imagery (and possibly also in the logo text, see note on this further below)<\/span><\/p>\n\n<p class=\"font_8\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">The desired general design approach is simple lines and solid colours (more summery than fall), so that it can be readily rendered into T-shirts, website and, again, possible as part of the final logo design
